==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cantabile
<hw>Can*ta"bi*le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[It.,
<ets>cantare</ets> to sing.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>In a
melodious, flowing style; in a singing style, as opposed to
<xex>bravura</xex>, <xex>recitativo</xex>, or
<xex>parlando</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cantabile</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cantabile
<hw>Can*ta"bi*le</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A piece
or passage, whether vocal or instrumental, peculiarly adapted to
singing; -- sometimes called <altname>cantilena</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cantabrian</ent>⟦br⟧
